A '''Germanophone''' is someone who speaks the [[German language]] either natively or by adoption. As an adjective it means "German-speaking." Germanophone countries include [[Germany]], [[Austria]], [[Liechtenstein]], and most of [[Switzerland]]. There are also sizable Germanophone communities in [[Belgium]] and [[Luxembourg]].

There are an estimated 120 million Germanophones world-wide.

